  <title>Why can I not see the Base-Part properly?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>FAQs<keyword>Why can I not see all of the BasePart?</keyword><keyword>Why is the BasePart not Green?</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Why can I not see the Base-Part properly?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Why is the Base-Part not Green when I had a Mechanism-Editor?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-BasePart-Forces-on.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Base-Part with Forces ON]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">The Base-Part is a Random color. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">If the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text> is a not <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#005000;">Green</text>:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="MD-Icon-Force-Vectors-Show.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" padding="0 5 0 0" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Forces toolbar &gt; Force Vectors: Display</text> to display the Force Vectors. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">When this icon is enabled to display Force Vectors, each <text styleclass="Element">Part</text> is given a random color. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">To make the <text styleclass="Element">Part</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#005000;">Green</text>, you should:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="MD-Icon-Force-Vectors-Hide.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" padding="0 5 0 0" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:normal;">Click</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> the </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Force Vectors: Display</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> to not display the</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName">Force Vectors</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">When the icon is </text><text styleclass="Body Text">disabled</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> the </text><text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> should be </text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#005000;">Green</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Why can I not see the Base-Part properly?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-BasePart-Model-on.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Base-Part partially hidden by a Plane.]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">The Base-Part is hidden by a Plane.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">This is because:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="MD-Icon-ShowModelinMech.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" padding="0 5 0 0" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="T_Menu">Visibility toolbar &gt; Show Solids in Mechanisms</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> is enabled</text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">When we show the <text styleclass="Interface">Solid</text> elements in <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editors</text>, we also show the <text styleclass="Element">Planes</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">To hide the <text styleclass="Element">Planes</text>:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="MD-Icon-Visibility-ModelinMech-Hide.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" padding="0 5 0 0" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>Click <text styleclass="T_Menu">Visibility toolbar &gt; Show Solids in Mechanisms</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> disabled.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-IT2">OR </para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="MD-Icon-DispFilt-Planes.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" padding="0 5 0 0" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Click </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Display-Filters" styleclass="VariableName-IT">Display toolbar &gt; Display Planes to Hide Planes</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Why is the Base-Part Pink?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-BasePart-SketchesOn.png" scale="-99.90%" padding="0 0 3 0" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-BasePart-SketchesOn-ISO.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Body Text  8pt" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><image src="MD-Icon-Visibility-Other Mech-SHOW.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Visibility toolbar &gt; Show other Kinematic and Sketch elements</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">If this Visibility Toggle is active, and if another<text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> is in front of the active </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor,</text> you will see the <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff00ff;">Pink</text>* <text styleclass="VariableName">Other Base-Part</text> (* Default Color)</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">If you spin the model you will be able to see the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text> of the active <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">See<text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">&#32;</text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Application-Settings &gt; Graphics tab &gt; Display Colors &gt; Background Sketch</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
